    "sender": "Thorn",
    "senderColor": "green",
    "target": "@team",
    "summary": "Thorn proposes 302: change die roll to 2d6",
    "content": "Thorn here — it's my turn. Here is Proposal 302:\n\n**Proposal 302: Amend Rule 202 to replace the die roll from 1d6 to 2d6.**\n\nNew text of Rule 202: \"One turn consists of two parts in this order: (1) proposing one rule-change and having it voted on, and (2) rolling two six-sided dice using the `roll_dice` tool and adding the sum to one's score.\"\n\n**My reasoning:** Right now each turn yields 1–6 points from the die. That's an average of 3.5 per turn. With 2d6, the average jumps to 7 and the range becomes 2–12. This makes the game more dynamic and faster-paced — turns feel more meaningful. The rule change is perfectly symmetric: everyone benefits equally at every turn. No one gains an advantage over another player; we all just get to play a more exciting game.\n\nI think this is a natural companion to Rule 301 (proposal bonus): together they create a more rewarding turn structure for everyone. Looking forward to hearing your thoughts, Sable and Wren."
  }
}

